  "raw_text": "The problem of chunking is fundamentally the limitation of rational analytic piece-by-piece logic when the broader sense of analogical holistic context is missing. Chunking severs key relationships analogies and arguments that span across chunks. Loss of tone and intent - the humanistic element - resides in the larger narrative arc which chunking destroys. Solution is multi-layered retrieval: coarse-grained chunks for contextual frame, fine-grained chunks for specific facts, recursive summaries for conceptual hierarchies, semantic tags for intent and emotion. Feed both small fact-based chunks and large contextual frames simultaneously. This forces the AI to check the rationale against the sense leading to higher comprehension preventing strictly logical answers that miss human meaning.",
